<br>
I have yet to see any focus applied to Tears of Marr and the same resists we see in other rain spells seems to apply to ToM as well.<br>
<br>
When looking at Damage per mana figures, initially ToM looks appealing<br>
<br>
ToM - 2550 dam for 450 mana = 5.66 dpm (damage per mana)<br>
SoS - 2740 dam for 640 mana = 4.28 dpm<br>
Draught of Eci - 950 dam for 255 mana = 3.73 dpm<br>
Ice spear - 1200 dam for 300 mana = 4 dpm<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, focus items do not seem to ToM, nor any AE spell.  I don't know of a single level 65 wizard who does not use at least 20% focus. Still though, its rare that one gets the full focus effect on each cast so I will modify the with focus numbers to realistic numbers one could expect on most casts<br>
<br>
ToM 1700 dam (I figure at least one resist per cast) 3.78 dpm<br>
SoS 3000 dam (seems reasonable) 4.69 dpm<br>
Eci 1050 dam 4.11 dpm<br>
Ice spear 1400 dam (using eci with it) 4.67 dpm<br>
<br>
Under these more realistic numbers(not using max possible) SoS and Ice spear seem to be the best bets and even draught of Eci seems a better choice then Tears of Marr. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kadathdreamfire>Kadath Dreamfire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1043<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/03 11:01:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26194.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://zorak.monmouth.edu/~posten/minigang.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tears of Marr</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the insights.  I suspect that it will be situational, as rains tend to be, where fast damage and low resists are expected.  I love rains myself, its just that their applicability has such a low occurance...<br>
<br>
